  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6765 sitting directly on the max negative gamma strike (-14.1B), dealers are forced to buy this dip aggressively while the regime flip into BREAKOUT mode means they'll amplify any directional move. The massive negative gamma wall from 6760-6770 creates a dangerous zone where dealer hedging will accelerate momentum in either direction, while 6780 represents the first meaningful positive gamma resistance where dealers would start selling into strength.\n\nKey battle zone is 6765-6780: break below 6760 triggers cascading dealer buying pressure down toward the 6430 flip strike, while any push through 6780 faces immediate dealer selling pressure but could momentum higher if 6800 positive gamma fails to hold.\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings as dealers amplify every move from this precarious negative gamma perch.",
